        <briefdescription>
<para>Resize the table to the smallest power-of-2 capacity that keeps load under 75%, clearing all tombstones in the process. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>If the input capacity is bigger than zero, the table will be resized to at least that capacity (rounded up to the next power of 2).</para>
<para>If the map is empty and targetCapacity is 0, the table is freed entirely (capacity becomes 0). If the current capacity is already optimal, this is a no-op.</para>
