    <briefdescription>
<para>A lightweight open-addressed hash map with linear probing. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Uses a single contiguous allocation (calloc) for the entry table. Power-of-2 capacity, grows at 75% load. Deletion uses tombstones.</para>
<para>Key requirements:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Must be trivially copyable (stored by value in entries).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Must support comparison to sentinels via ==.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>OpenHashMapTraits&lt;Key&gt; must provide <ref refid="classDali_1_1Integration_1_1OpenHashMap_1abb6fc72af953dc13088447ee0d2e27b4" kindref="member">Empty()</ref> and Tombstone() sentinels that are distinct from each other and from any valid key.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Key</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Key type (typically a pointer) </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Value</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Mapped value type </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Hash</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Hash functor: size_t operator()(const Key&amp;) const </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>KeyEqual</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Equality functor: bool operator()(const Key&amp;, const Key&amp;) const </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
